      vestingAnalysis: "As Bitcoin is a fully decentralized and widely distributed asset, there are no traditional \'vesting schedules\' in the sense of locked tokens for a team or private investors. Its supply distribution is governed by mining and market dynamics.",
      teamAnalysis: "Bitcoin was created by an anonymous entity or group known as Satoshi Nakamoto. There is no central \'team\' in the traditional corporate sense; development is driven by a decentralized community of developers, contributors, and miners.",
      fundingAnalysis: "Bitcoin was not launched via a traditional funding round or ICO. Its initial distribution was through mining, allowing anyone to participate and earn coins, fostering a decentralized and open-source development model.",
      ecosystemAnalysis: "The Bitcoin ecosystem is vast, encompassing numerous exchanges, wallets, payment processors, layer-2 solutions like the Lightning Network, and a global community of users, developers, and businesses. Its network effect is the strongest in crypto.",
      airdropPotential: "Bitcoin itself does not have \'airdrop potential\' in the typical sense, as it is a foundational cryptocurrency. However, forks or new projects built on Bitcoin\'s layer-2 solutions or sidechains may offer airdrops.",
      marketCap: "Bitcoin\'s market capitalization fluctuates significantly with price movements, generally ranging from hundreds of billions to over a trillion US dollars, making it the largest crypto asset.",
